SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Labour Force\, Australia\, April 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS latest release pag
 e\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Employment / Payrolls / Labour Force\n\
 n• Measures: Change in employment\, unemployment\, participation and l
 abour-market strength.\n\n• Usual market effect: Stronger-than-forecas
 t jobs data is usually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bo
 nds if it increases rate-hike expectations.\n\n• Why traders care: Job
 s data is a major driver of interest-rate expectations\, consumer spendi
 ng expectations and recession-risk pricing.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly.\n
 \n• Notes: For the US\, Non-Farm Payrolls is one of the most market-mo
 ving releases. For Australia\, Labour Force data is important for RBA ex
 pectations.\n\n• Acronyms: NFP = Non-Farm Payrolls\; ABS = Australian 
 Bureau of Statistics\; BLS = Bureau of Labor Statistics.\n\nOfficial sou
 rce: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/labour/employment-and-unemploymen
 t/labour-force-australia/apr-2026
