SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Producer Price Indexes\, Australia\, June 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nSource: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nO
 fficial ABS series page release date. Time zone shown by ABS: AEST.\n\nE
 xplainer:\n• What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change 
 in prices received by producers for goods and services.\n\n• Usual mar
 ket effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish for the local curren
 cy if traders expect producer inflation to flow through to consumer infl
 ation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can provide an early signal of infla
 tion pressure before it reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly in 
 the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usually less market
 -moving than CPI\, but it can still matter when inflation is the main ma
 cro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n\nOfficial sour
 ce: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflatio
 n/producer-price-indexes-australia\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Produc
 er Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices received by producers f
 or goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast 
 PPI can be bullish for the local currency if traders expect producer inf
 lation to flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: P
 PI can provide an early signal of inflation pressure before it reaches c
 onsumers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n
 \n• Notes: PPI is usually less market-moving than CPI\, but it can sti
 ll matter when inflation is the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI =
  Producer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statis
 tics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/producer-price-indexes-australi
 a
