 ice in higher interest rates.\n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the
  most watched inflation indicators because it can quickly shift central-
 bank rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian 
 CPI has both monthly indicator releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n
 • Notes: Core CPI removes volatile items such as food and energy to gi
 ve a cleaner read on underlying inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI
  = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/stat
 istics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/consumer-price-index-australi
 a\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Consumer Price Index\n\n• Measures: C
 hange in the prices paid by consumers for a basket of goods and services
 .\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually 
 bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds\, because markets m
 ay price in higher interest rates.\n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one o
 f the most watched inflation indicators because it can quickly shift cen
 tral-bank rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Austra
 lian CPI has both monthly indicator releases and quarterly CPI releases.
 \n\n• Notes: Core CPI removes volatile items such as food and energy t
 o give a cleaner read on underlying inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms:
  CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/
 statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/consumer-price-index-aust
 ralia
