DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nSource: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nO
 fficial ABS series page release date. Time zone shown by ABS: AEST.\n\nE
 xplainer:\n• What it is: Employment / Payrolls / Labour Force\n\n• M
 easures: Change in employment\, unemployment\, participation and labour-
 market strength.\n\n• Usual market effect: Stronger-than-forecast jobs
  data is usually bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds if
  it increases rate-hike expectations.\n\n• Why traders care: Jobs data
  is a major driver of interest-rate expectations\, consumer spending exp
 ectations and recession-risk pricing.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly.\n\n• 
 Notes: For the US\, Non-Farm Payrolls is one of the most market-moving r
 eleases. For Australia\, Labour Force data is important for RBA expectat
 ions.\n\n• Acronyms: NFP = Non-Farm Payrolls\; ABS = Australian Bureau
  of Statistics\; BLS = Bureau of Labor Statistics.\n\nOfficial source: h
 ttps://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/labour/employment-and-unemployment/labo
 ur-force-australia\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Employment / Payrolls 
 / Labour Force\n\n• Measures: Change in employment\, unemployment\, pa
 rticipation and labour-market strength.\n\n• Usual market effect: Stro
 nger-than-forecast jobs data is usually bullish for the local currency a
 nd bearish for bonds if it increases rate-hike expectations.\n\n• Why 
 traders care: Jobs data is a major driver of interest-rate expectations\
 , consumer spending expectations and recession-risk pricing.\n\n• Freq
 uency: Monthly.\n\n• Notes: For the US\, Non-Farm Payrolls is one of t
 he most market-moving releases. For Australia\, Labour Force data is imp
 ortant for RBA expectations.\n\n• Acronyms: NFP = Non-Farm Payrolls\; 
 ABS = Australian Bureau of Statistics\; BLS = Bureau of Labor Statistics
 .\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/labour/employmen
 t-and-unemployment/labour-force-australia
