SUMMARY:🔥 AU ABS: Producer Price Indexes\, Australia
DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nSource: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nR
 eference period\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n
 • Measures: Change in prices received by producers for goods and servi
 ces.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish
  for the local currency if traders expect producer inflation to flow thr
 ough to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can provide an 
 early signal of inflation pressure before it reaches consumers.\n\n• F
 requency: Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI i
 s usually less market-moving than CPI\, but it can still matter when inf
 lation is the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price In
 dex.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-
 releases/202610\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n
 • Measures: Change in prices received by producers for goods and servi
 ces.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish
  for the local currency if traders expect producer inflation to flow thr
 ough to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can provide an 
 early signal of inflation pressure before it reaches consumers.\n\n• F
 requency: Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI i
 s usually less market-moving than CPI\, but it can still matter when inf
 lation is the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price In
 dex.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-
 releases/202610
