SUMMARY:🔥 US Fed: FOMC Interest Rate Decision
DESCRIPTION:Source: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nO
 fficial Federal Reserve monthly calendar FOMC meeting entry.\n\nExplaine
 r:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest
 -rate decision\, policy statement and guidance from the central bank.\n\
 n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually
  bullish for the local currency and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-
 expected guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bullish for bo
 nds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly affect int
 erest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.
 \n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• Notes: The m
 arket often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to the state
 ment\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Fe
 deral Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOffici
 al source: https://www.federalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-december.htm\n
 \nExplainer:\n• What it is: Central Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures
 : Interest-rate decision\, policy statement and guidance from the centra
 l bank.\n\n• Usual market effect: More hawkish-than-expected guidance 
