 vish-than-expected guidance is usually bearish for the currency and bull
 ish for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-bank decisions directly 
 affect interest rates\, currency valuation\, bond yields and equity risk
  appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several times per year.\n\n• No
 tes: The market often reacts not only to the rate decision\, but also to
  the statement\, forecasts\, press conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms:
  FOMC = Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.
